This is Foreman -- a lifecycle management tool for physical and virtual servers.

## Additional Context
- Before starting any task, run load_skill("foreman-docs") to review accumulated project knowledge (gotchas, patterns).
- The docs loaded via foreman-docs are read-only copies deployed by bootstrap. The source of truth is ~/cosmic-unconscious/projects/foreman/docs/. Never edit the copies under .agents/skills/.
- At the end of each session, remind the user to update the source docs in ~/cosmic-unconscious/projects/foreman/docs/ and commit in that repo (cd ~/cosmic-unconscious && git add -A && git commit).

## Layout
- Code: this directory
- Katello and other plugins mount into this app via Rails Engines
- Plugin registration: bundler.d/*.local.rb

## Key Directories
- Models (~86): app/models/
- Controllers: app/controllers/
- Services: app/services/
- Views: app/views/
- Tests: test/ (minitest with factories)
- GraphQL: app/graphql/

## Running Things
All commands run from this directory.
- Rails console: bundle exec rails console
- Tests: bundle exec rake test
- Single test: bundle exec ruby -Itest test/path/to/test.rb

## Relationship to Katello
- Katello is a plugin registered in bundler.d/katello.local.rb
- Foreman provides the host model, RBAC system, smart proxy infrastructure
- Katello extends Foreman hosts with content facets
